Copy Constructor:

Copy constructor (default) used to copy one object values to into another object.

int main(){
teacher t2;
teacher t1(t2); <---- this is copy constructor.
}

There are two types of Copy that is shallow copy & Deep Copy.

Shallow Copy: A Shallow copy of an object copies of all the member values from one object to another object.
e.g. it's simply create the refernce pointer and share the reference of that pointer when create a new pointer.

Deep Copy: A deep copy, on the other hand, not only copies the member values but also make copies of any dynamically allocated memory
that the members that the members point to. let's look into a example we create 1 object and it's have name and number values and I 
want to copy the details of that object into new object but I want to change a number value in that object so I need to create a new
pointer that is called dynamically allocate that number to that object.

